1
00:00:00,042 --> 00:00:01,959
The toilet was in the prison

2
00:00:02,959 --> 00:00:04,209
They don’t open the door for you

3
00:00:05,709 --> 00:00:08,751
In the prison, meaning when you are in the cell

4
00:00:08,792 --> 00:00:10,209
There was a toilet in it

5
00:00:12,417 --> 00:00:13,709
The toilet was in it

6
00:00:13,959 --> 00:00:18,042
So there was no need to tell them you wanted to go out

7
00:00:18,417 --> 00:00:19,626
It was in the room

8
00:00:21,334 --> 00:00:25,250
But in another prison, the cell was separate from the toilet

9
00:00:27,918 --> 00:00:30,042
Interviewer: And when you go to the toilet, are you alone?

10
00:00:30,083 --> 00:00:31,542
Yes, there’s no one else

11
00:00:31,876 --> 00:00:37,876
It’s in the same cell, placed in one corner

12
00:00:38,751 --> 00:00:40,125
And in the same prison cell

13
00:00:42,584 --> 00:00:46,834
Interviewer: Was water and everything available there?

14
00:00:49,417 --> 00:00:53,834
Meaning, could you use water as you wanted?

15
00:00:54,876 --> 00:00:57,459
Yes, there was water the first time

16
00:00:58,584 --> 00:01:03,209
The first time, there was water and you could use it as you wanted

17
00:01:03,959 --> 00:01:06,792
And it was available later on too

18
00:01:07,918 --> 00:01:11,751
Interviewer: Was the place in the toilet clean?

19
00:01:12,709 --> 00:01:14,584
Not really

20
00:01:16,459 --> 00:01:17,667
It was so-so

21
00:01:20,250 --> 00:01:22,083
It wasn’t 100 percent clean

22
00:01:22,667 --> 00:01:24,626
And not 100 percent dirty

23
00:01:25,042 --> 00:01:26,209
It was in between

24
00:01:26,834 --> 00:01:29,042
Interviewer: Tell me, how did you shower?

25
00:01:29,209 --> 00:01:30,375
There were no showers

26
00:01:30,876 --> 00:01:34,083
Do you want to shower with tap water in freezing cold

27
00:01:34,751 --> 00:01:36,042
I was imprisoned in cold weather

28
00:01:36,083 --> 00:01:40,417
That was in February, the first time

29
00:01:41,792 --> 00:01:43,959
No, the first time was in December

30
00:01:46,417 --> 00:01:48,751
And the second time was in February, it was also cold

31
00:01:50,250 --> 00:01:52,834
You couldn’t shower, when we got out we showered at home

32
00:01:53,709 --> 00:01:54,959
Interviewer: In which month was that?

33
00:01:56,292 --> 00:01:58,375
In December and in February

34
00:02:00,751 --> 00:02:04,000
Interviewer: So you didn’t shower at all?

35
00:02:04,042 --> 00:02:07,834
Didn’t you ask them to let you go to the bathroom to shower?

36
00:02:07,876 --> 00:02:10,500
No, I didn’t ask them that

37
00:02:12,250 --> 00:02:17,167
I didn’t ask, we only did <i>wudu</i> [ablution] for prayer

38
00:02:19,042 --> 00:02:20,751
And prayer was mandatory

39
00:02:22,876 --> 00:02:25,375
It wasn’t optional, whether you wanted to or not

40
00:02:26,709 --> 00:02:30,876
Everyone, before ISIS or after they left

41
00:02:31,417 --> 00:02:33,792
Prayer was between him and his God

42
00:02:34,209 --> 00:02:37,083
But for them, you had to pray compulsorily

43
00:02:39,417 --> 00:02:41,667
Interviewer: Was the water cold or hot?

44
00:02:41,918 --> 00:02:43,959
It was very cold, it was tap water

45
00:02:45,500 --> 00:02:48,209
Also the tank water is colder than the tap water

46
00:02:49,375 --> 00:02:51,834
Because it was winter, and there was no hot water
